sketch.compiler.ast.core.exprs

Class ExprBinary

  • java.lang.Object
    • sketch.compiler.ast.core.FENode
      • sketch.compiler.ast.core.exprs.Expression
        • sketch.compiler.ast.core.exprs.ExprBinary

  • public class ExprBinary
extends Expression
    A binary expression. This has two child expressions, which must be non-null, and an operator. The child expressions are ordered (because a-b is different from b-a).
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    David Maze <dmaze@cag.lcs.mit.edu>

    • Constructor Detail

      • ExprBinary

        public ExprBinary(FENode node,
                  int op,
                  Expression left,
                  Expression right)
        Create a new binary expression given the operation and the left and right child nodes. Requires that op is a valid operator code and that left and right are non-null.
        Parameters:
        context - file and line number this expression corresponds to
        op - BINOP_ operator combining the two expressions
        left - expression on the left of the operator
        right - expression on the right of the operator
